The President of the United States received an update on the situation in Turkey from his national security and foreign policy team. He expressed support for the democratically-elected government of Turkey and instructed his team to work with their Turkish counterparts to ensure the safety of diplomatic missions, U.S. servicemembers, and their dependents. Although there were no indications of American casualties, the President expressed condolences for the loss of life and stressed the importance of all parties in Turkey acting within the rule of law to prevent further violence or instability. The President also emphasized the need for continued Turkish cooperation in combating terrorism. He requested ongoing updates on the situation.